handist.collections.dist

Class CachableArray<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • apgas.util.PlaceLocalObject
      • handist.collections.dist.CachableArray<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the elements handled by the CachableArray
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    apgas.util.SerializableWithReplace, Serializable, Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, List<T>

    public class CachableArray<T>
extends apgas.util.PlaceLocalObject
implements List<T>, apgas.util.SerializableWithReplace
    A class for handling objects using the Master-Proxy mechanism. The master place has the body of each elements. The proxy places have the branch of each elements. Note: In the current implementation, there are some limitations. o The first place of the PlaceGroup is selected as the master place automatically. o To add any new elements is not allowed. The elements are assigned only in the construction.
    See Also:

      • broadcast

        public <U> void broadcast(Function<T,U> pack,
                          BiConsumer<T,U> unpack)
        Broadcast from master place to proxy place, packing elements using the specified function. It is assumed that the type U is declared as a struct and that it does not contain any reference.

        Note: Currently, this method is implemented in too simple way.

        Type Parameters:
        U - type used to represent the elements of this instance and that is going to be transfered to remote hosts. In the implementation of the pack and unpack, the programmer may choose to use T, but this allows any other custom type to be used.
        Parameters:
        pack - a function which packs the elements of the master node.
        unpack - a function which unpacks the received data and inserts the unpacked data into the instance local to each proxy.
